		<h1 class="page-title">Welcome to ECPL!</h1>
		<div class="entry clearfix">
			<h2>Library Board seeking new members</h2>
<p>Please call, fax, write or e-mail the township by May 19, 2016 if you would like to be considered for membership on the <span><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Edwardsburgh Cardinal</strong><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> P</span></strong></span><strong><u>ublic Library Board.</u></strong></p>
<p>Meetings take place on the last Tuesday of every month and rotate between the Spencerville and Cardinal libraries.</p>
<p>Applicants are requested to provide their complete name and address and a brief summary of their particular interests and experience to:</p>
<p>Email: mail@twpec.ca</p>
<p>Mail:    Shelbi Deacon</p>
<p>18 Centre St<br />
PO Box 129<br />
Spencerville, ON<br />
K0E1X0</p>
<p>Fax:     613-658-3445</p>
<h2>What&#8217;s available at the library</h2>
<p>The Edwardsburgh Cardinal Public Library has a collection of more than 87,000 print and e-resources including books, books on CD, videos, magazines, ebooks and downloadable audiobooks. Inter-Library Loan is also available.</p>
<p>Computers High Speed Internet access is available on our computers free of charge. Photocopying, computer printing, and fax services are also available.</p>
<p>The Edwardsburgh Cardinal Public Library also offers an assortment of community programs for residents of all ages. Check out our Programs pages for more information.</p>
<h2>Locations &amp; Hours</h2>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<h4>Spencerville Branch &#8212; 5 Henderson Street</h4>
<p>Monday &#8211; CLOSED<br />
Tuesday &#8211; 2 &#8211; 6 p.m.<br />
Wednesday &#8211; 5 &#8211; 8:30 p.m.<br />
Thursday &#8211; 2 &#8211; 6 p.m.<br />
Friday &#8211; CLOSED<br />
Saturday &#8211; 10 a.m. &#8211; 1:30 p.m.<br />
Sunday &#8211; CLOSED</td>
<td>
<h4>Cardinal Branch &#8212; 618 County Road 2</h4>
<p>Monday &#8211; 5:30 &#8211; 8 p.m.<br />
Tuesday &#8211; 1 &#8211; 4:30 p.m.<br />
Wednesday -5:30 &#8211; 8 p.m.<br />
Thursday &#8211; 1 &#8211; 4:30 p.m.<br />
Friday &#8211; CLOSED<br />
Saturday &#8211; 9 a.m. &#8211; 12 noon<br />
Sunday &#8211; CLOSED</td>
</tr>
